The paper proposes a method for modeling event sequences using Recurrent Neural Networks (RNNs) and applies it to a predictive maintenance problem using a log dataset from a global bank. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE), social and information networks (cs.SI), and information theory (cs.IT).
